WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:01:27.796 --> 00:01:30.882
<i>Don't be. be. be afraid</i>

3
00:01:31.382 --> 00:01:35.595
<i>Don't be. be. be. be afraid</i>

4
00:01:35.678 --> 00:01:41.017
BAKI-DOU: THE INVINCIBLE SAMURAI

5
00:01:44.395 --> 00:01:47.273
<i>Everybody practices running upstairs.</i>

6
00:01:47.357 --> 00:01:49.025
<i>but where's the fun in that?</i>

7
00:01:50.318 --> 00:01:52.028
<i>Now. running down them…</i>

8
00:01:53.404 --> 00:01:55.115
<i>…all the way</i>…

9
00:02:00.120 --> 00:02:01.162
<i>…in one go!</i>

10
00:02:03.456 --> 00:02:05.250
<i>Legs and arms into it!</i>

11
00:02:05.333 --> 00:02:06.501
<i>Keep falling!</i>

12
00:02:06.584 --> 00:02:08.128
<i>And the only way not to fall</i>

13
00:02:08.211 --> 00:02:10.505
<i>is to go even faster.</i>

14
00:02:10.588 --> 00:02:11.881
<i>right to the bottom!</i>

15
00:02:12.465 --> 00:02:14.300
<i>Oh. not again. Right now?</i>

16
00:02:14.384 --> 00:02:16.386
<i>At a time like this?</i>
<i>How is that even possible?</i>

17
00:02:16.469 --> 00:02:17.887
<i>There it is!</i>

18
00:02:17.971 --> 00:02:19.639
<i>Another yawn?!</i>

19
00:02:21.391 --> 00:02:23.893
<i>I knew that would happen.</i>
<i>Still. I'm kinda surprised.</i>

20
00:02:28.481 --> 00:02:31.526
<i>I never thought running downstairs</i>
<i>would be that boring.</i>

21
00:02:37.615 --> 00:02:39.117
<i>I'm so bored.</i>

22
00:02:44.497 --> 00:02:46.749
<i>I don't care about this belt anymore.</i>

23
00:02:48.626 --> 00:02:52.547
<i>I'm getting tired of these pointless</i>
<i>"pound-for-pound" matches.</i>

24
00:02:55.383 --> 00:02:57.552
<i>I've been the champion for seven years.</i>

25
00:02:58.136 --> 00:03:00.555
- I've won too many damn times.
- Huh? Hey!

26
00:03:01.639 --> 00:03:03.224
What's the matter with…

27
00:03:03.308 --> 00:03:06.477
<i>I've had my fill.</i>

28
00:03:08.229 --> 00:03:10.899
<i>There's nothing else</i>
<i>this sport can give me.</i>

29
00:03:13.067 --> 00:03:15.612
<i>I don't wanna be known</i>
<i>as the best anymore.</i>

30
00:03:17.322 --> 00:03:19.741
<i>I wanna be known as the strongest.</i>

31
00:03:19.824 --> 00:03:20.992
Huh?

32
00:03:22.827 --> 00:03:24.495
All right. that's enough!

33
00:03:29.834 --> 00:03:33.755
But. Mr. Atlas. I don't understand.
Why go to Japan?

34
00:03:34.422 --> 00:03:36.257
That's obvious. isn't it?

35
00:03:37.634 --> 00:03:41.387
<i>Everyone knows the strongest man</i>
<i>in the world calls Japan his home.</i>

36
00:03:44.557 --> 00:03:46.935
{\an8}Can you explain why you want to fight?

37
00:03:47.018 --> 00:03:50.480
Seems to me you've already gotten
your fair share of recognition.

38
00:03:50.563 --> 00:03:51.773
Am I wrong?

39
00:03:52.649 --> 00:03:55.777
I have. but then I saw
that fight between father and son.

40
00:03:57.320 --> 00:04:00.782
Well. isn't that interesting?
And what did you think of the fight?

41
00:04:02.158 --> 00:04:04.911
Never in my life
have I seen the human body move

42
00:04:04.994 --> 00:04:06.537
with such grace and beauty.

43
00:04:06.621 --> 00:04:09.207
So… that was the impetus.

44
00:04:09.290 --> 00:04:11.251
Shogun Tokugawa.

45
00:04:11.751 --> 00:04:13.044
it's come to my attention

46
00:04:13.127 --> 00:04:15.713
that you're promoting that boy.
Baki Hanma.

47
00:04:18.549 --> 00:04:19.717
Hmm.

48
00:04:19.801 --> 00:04:21.928
You think you can beat Baki Hanma?

49
00:04:22.011 --> 00:04:23.596
Well. I am here. aren't I?

50
00:04:23.680 --> 00:04:26.474
I came to the other side
of the world to find out.

51
00:04:26.557 --> 00:04:30.478
I'm assuming you're aware that this battle
will be light on rules. hmm?

52
00:04:30.561 --> 00:04:32.981
That's precisely why I came.

53
00:04:34.315 --> 00:04:37.902
It's no secret
you make over 400 million yen per match.

54
00:04:37.986 --> 00:04:39.654
I do. yes.

55
00:04:39.737 --> 00:04:42.532
But in this match you're promoting.
I'm not looking to be paid.

56
00:04:42.615 --> 00:04:45.660
The title of "The Strongest on Earth"
will be payment enough.

57
00:04:45.743 --> 00:04:49.163
I don't know. that kid fights pretty hard.

58
00:04:49.247 --> 00:04:51.165
And I do too.

59
00:04:51.249 --> 00:04:53.042
Well. in that case…

60
00:04:55.753 --> 00:04:57.755
are you in any condition to fight?

61
00:04:58.840 --> 00:05:01.551
I'm always ready.
We could have the fight tonight.

62
00:05:01.634 --> 00:05:04.178
- All right. then. Tonight it is.
- Tonight?!

63
00:05:04.762 --> 00:05:06.681
The match will go forward this evening.

64
00:05:06.764 --> 00:05:09.600
- Oh. well. let's not rush into this.
- Is there a problem?

65
00:05:09.684 --> 00:05:12.645
No! No. no. no. no. no!
I've got no problem at all.

66
00:05:12.729 --> 00:05:15.440
It's just that tonight is a little sudden.

67
00:05:15.523 --> 00:05:18.693
And Baki Hanma hasn't even been informed
about the match yet.

68
00:05:21.070 --> 00:05:24.824
Mm-hmm. I assure you.
he's got nothing else to do tonight.

69
00:05:24.907 --> 00:05:27.493
So he'd be killing time with our fight?

70
00:05:27.577 --> 00:05:30.204
There is something you should know.
Mr. Atlas.

71
00:05:30.288 --> 00:05:32.707
Baki Hanma will never pass on a fight.

72
00:05:32.790 --> 00:05:33.916
Oh…

73
00:05:34.542 --> 00:05:37.712
Baki is the strongest
because he never refuses a fight.

74
00:05:37.795 --> 00:05:40.214
Anyone. anywhere. anytime.

75
00:05:47.805 --> 00:05:50.350
Yes. that's right. It would be tonight.

76
00:05:50.433 --> 00:05:53.102
Against an American.
some kind of martial artist.

77
00:05:53.186 --> 00:05:55.396
Mixed martial arts. Mm-hmm.

78
00:05:56.022 --> 00:05:57.690
Yeah. he's… he's a heavyweight.

79
00:05:58.191 --> 00:05:59.942
That's right. Mm-hmm.

80
00:06:00.443 --> 00:06:02.945
All right. perfect. Uh-huh. Okay. thanks.

81
00:06:03.029 --> 00:06:05.239
- He says he'll do it!
- Oh… oh.

82
00:06:06.449 --> 00:06:08.368
<i>Soon my opponent will arrive.</i>

83
00:06:08.451 --> 00:06:12.121
<i>He'll come striding through that doorway.</i>
<i>The one they call the strongest.</i>

84
00:06:21.964 --> 00:06:22.882
<i>This…</i>

85
00:06:24.467 --> 00:06:25.426
<i>kid?</i>

86
00:06:25.510 --> 00:06:27.136
That's <i>Baki Hanma?</i>

87
00:06:27.845 --> 00:06:28.721
<i>Hmm.</i>

88
00:06:29.222 --> 00:06:32.308
<i>It's definitely the same face</i>
<i>I saw on the video.</i>

89
00:06:32.392 --> 00:06:33.643
<i>But he's so</i>…

90
00:06:33.726 --> 00:06:35.019
<i>so small.</i>

91
00:06:35.103 --> 00:06:36.354
<i>Is he a featherweight?</i>

92
00:06:36.437 --> 00:06:37.855
<i>Lightweight at best.</i>

93
00:06:37.939 --> 00:06:40.149
<i>I mean. he's only half my size.</i>

94
00:06:40.233 --> 00:06:44.153
<i>I see now. Look at all the scars</i>
<i>carved into his body.</i>

95
00:06:44.237 --> 00:06:45.571
<i>And at such a young age.</i>

96
00:06:45.655 --> 00:06:47.657
<i>No doubt this kid is a seasoned warrior.</i>

97
00:06:47.740 --> 00:06:49.659
<i>Each scar. each and every one.</i>

98
00:06:49.742 --> 00:06:52.662
<i>are all pieces of this boy's history.</i>

99
00:07:06.008 --> 00:07:08.428
<i>What the fuck did I just see?</i>

100
00:07:08.511 --> 00:07:12.098
<i>In front of me is a boy</i>
<i>who could easily be mistaken for a girl.</i>

101
00:07:12.181 --> 00:07:13.182
<i>And behind him.</i>

102
00:07:13.266 --> 00:07:17.186
<i>a monster that feels both new</i>
<i>and strangely familiar.</i>

103
00:07:25.486 --> 00:07:27.280
Excuse me. Sir?

104
00:07:27.780 --> 00:07:29.699
- Mr. Atlas?
- Uh…

105
00:07:29.782 --> 00:07:32.034
Are you ready to begin. Mr. Atlas?

106
00:07:32.785 --> 00:07:34.203
Oh. I'm sorry.

107
00:07:34.829 --> 00:07:36.247
I'll say it once more.

108
00:07:36.330 --> 00:07:38.791
All weapons are prohibited. That is all.

109
00:07:38.875 --> 00:07:41.711
Fight fair and square.
and may the strongest man win.

110
00:07:44.046 --> 00:07:46.424
<i>Now. that's a simple rule.</i>

111
00:07:46.507 --> 00:07:48.968
<i>As long as I don't use weapons.</i>
<i>anything goes.</i>

112
00:07:49.051 --> 00:07:53.097
Hmm. You're aware that this battle
will be light on rules. hmm?

113
00:07:53.181 --> 00:07:55.141
<i>This is exactly what I wanted.</i>

114
00:07:55.224 --> 00:07:56.559
- Sam Atlas!
- Huh?

115
00:07:56.642 --> 00:07:59.145
Sam Atlas! Sam Atlas! Sam Atlas!

116
00:07:59.228 --> 00:08:01.606
- Sam Atlas!
- <i>They're calling my name?</i>

117
00:08:01.689 --> 00:08:03.357
Sam Atlas!

118
00:08:03.441 --> 00:08:05.818
Sam Atlas! Sam Atlas!

119
00:08:05.902 --> 00:08:08.613
<i>Are they cheering for the underdog?</i>

120
00:08:08.696 --> 00:08:10.114
Sam Atlas!

121
00:08:10.198 --> 00:08:14.702
<i>Are they implying that a victory</i>
<i>is unlikely for me. a heavyweight?</i>

122
00:08:15.203 --> 00:08:19.874
<i>How can their faith in this puny child</i>
<i>be so unshakable?</i>

123
00:08:19.957 --> 00:08:22.585
<i>It should be obvious</i>
<i>to anyone looking at us</i>

124
00:08:22.668 --> 00:08:25.129
<i>that Baki Hanma weighs</i>
<i>half as much as I do.</i>

125
00:08:25.713 --> 00:08:29.091
<i>Even the legendary boxer who fought</i>
<i>in ten different weight classes.</i>

126
00:08:29.175 --> 00:08:32.470
<i>Manny Pacquiao. wouldn't dare</i>
<i>challenge a heavyweight to a fight.</i>

127
00:08:32.970 --> 00:08:36.390
<i>Weight difference is a wall</i>
<i>that not even legends can overcome.</i>

128
00:08:37.016 --> 00:08:40.144
<i>Baki Hanma.</i>
<i>what is this magic that you use?</i>

129
00:08:42.230 --> 00:08:45.149
<i>How will you try</i>
<i>to take on someone like me?!</i>

130
00:08:45.733 --> 00:08:48.861
<i>Ah. I can't wait to find out!</i>

131
00:08:53.449 --> 00:08:55.201
<i>He's a flawless fighter.</i>

132
00:08:56.869 --> 00:08:59.580
<i>He executed a perfect victory.</i>

133
00:08:59.664 --> 00:09:01.082
<i>and in a matter of seconds.</i>

134
00:09:01.165 --> 00:09:05.294
<i>In what seemed like the blink of an eye.</i>
<i>the entire match was settled.</i>

135
00:09:06.796 --> 00:09:08.714
<i>I knew it when I first saw him.</i>

136
00:09:09.507 --> 00:09:12.969
<i>Here I was. brimming with excitement</i>
<i>at the prospect of a fight.</i>

137
00:09:13.052 --> 00:09:16.013
<i>but Baki. his expression.</i>
<i>his body language</i>…

138
00:09:16.097 --> 00:09:17.765
<i>He was clearly bored.</i>

139
00:09:18.266 --> 00:09:20.685
<i>I forcefully stomped my foot down.</i>

140
00:09:21.352 --> 00:09:23.896
<i>then followed</i>
<i>with a high kick at close range.</i>

141
00:09:23.980 --> 00:09:25.690
<i>But that was all a feint.</i>

142
00:09:25.773 --> 00:09:28.442
<i>I came in with a hidden straight</i>
<i>that I thought would connect.</i>

143
00:09:28.526 --> 00:09:29.944
<i>But he dodged it.</i>

144
00:09:30.611 --> 00:09:33.114
<i>And right then. he grabbed me.</i>

145
00:09:34.949 --> 00:09:37.243
<i>This wasn't any kind of human strength.</i>

146
00:09:37.326 --> 00:09:38.703
<i>I couldn't pry him off.</i>

147
00:09:38.786 --> 00:09:41.622
<i>and my grip strength is almost 300 pounds.</i>

148
00:09:42.331 --> 00:09:44.375
<i>And then he apparently shook me.</i>

149
00:09:44.959 --> 00:09:46.627
<i>That's all that I can remember.</i>

150
00:09:47.128 --> 00:09:48.129
<i>I blacked out.</i>

151
00:09:48.212 --> 00:09:52.383
<i>because my brain was being slammed</i>
<i>up against the inner walls of my skull.</i>

152
00:09:52.466 --> 00:09:54.677
<i>Repeatedly and incessantly.</i>

153
00:09:55.886 --> 00:09:59.390
<i>No room for ifs or buts.</i>
<i>A truly decisive victory.</i>

154
00:10:01.475 --> 00:10:05.021
<i>What sticks with me most</i>
<i>is what I saw in the end.</i>

155
00:10:08.399 --> 00:10:09.400
<i>He's a nice guy.</i>

156
00:10:11.485 --> 00:10:13.404
<i>He didn't wanna add insult to injury.</i>

157
00:10:14.113 --> 00:10:18.075
<i>I know because I saw him</i>
<i>trying to stifle his yawn.</i>

158
00:10:22.288 --> 00:10:24.290
The prime minister is waiting for you.

159
00:10:24.373 --> 00:10:26.167
Then he can wait a little more.

160
00:10:26.250 --> 00:10:27.543
Understood. sir.

161
00:10:28.127 --> 00:10:31.589
Is it me.
or does the tower look a little twisted?

162
00:10:31.672 --> 00:10:35.593
Of course it does. It is DNA. after all.

163
00:10:35.676 --> 00:10:37.928
Huh? D… DNA?

164
00:10:40.890 --> 00:10:43.768
Allow me to welcome you.
honored Prime Minister.

165
00:10:43.851 --> 00:10:46.562
The staff and myself
have been awaiting your arrival.

166
00:10:48.105 --> 00:10:49.065
I. uh…

167
00:10:49.690 --> 00:10:51.734
My apologies. Prime Minister.

168
00:10:51.817 --> 00:10:55.571
My name is Hitoshi Nonomura.
I work as the project's team leader.

169
00:10:55.655 --> 00:10:58.074
Team leader? Okay.

170
00:10:58.157 --> 00:10:59.659
Mr. Prime Minister.

171
00:10:59.742 --> 00:11:02.078
the wheels have already been
set in motion.

172
00:11:02.161 --> 00:11:04.789
I. uh. I'm not sure what you mean.

173
00:11:04.872 --> 00:11:06.332
We can't back out of it now.

174
00:11:06.415 --> 00:11:08.376
Uh. my lord. I mean no disrespect.

175
00:11:08.459 --> 00:11:12.213
but I'm afraid I haven't been informed
of any of the specifics or details

176
00:11:12.296 --> 00:11:13.589
of today's meeting.

177
00:11:13.673 --> 00:11:15.549
I was just told to come in workwear.

178
00:11:22.056 --> 00:11:24.100
We won't be making any stops.

179
00:11:24.183 --> 00:11:26.143
This elevator will take us
straight to the lab.

180
00:11:26.227 --> 00:11:28.479
366 meters underground.

181
00:11:29.563 --> 00:11:32.441
<i>What on earth</i>
<i>could this be about? Underground?</i>

182
00:11:32.525 --> 00:11:34.276
<i>And more than 300 meters?</i>

183
00:11:34.777 --> 00:11:36.987
<i>All beneath Skytree. no less?</i>

184
00:11:37.071 --> 00:11:38.572
<i>Why is it buried so deep?</i>

185
00:11:39.073 --> 00:11:42.535
{\an8}- How has Mr. Honer been doing lately?
- He's been waiting for you.

186
00:11:43.119 --> 00:11:46.080
<i>What exactly</i>
<i>are they planning on showing me?</i>

187
00:11:50.334 --> 00:11:53.254
Wonderful to see you again. Mr. Tokugawa.

188
00:11:53.337 --> 00:11:55.965
<i>Something like this under Skytree?</i>

189
00:11:56.048 --> 00:11:58.926
<i>This is unbelievable.</i>
<i>How did they do all this?</i>

190
00:11:59.009 --> 00:12:00.261
<i>I never heard about this.</i>

191
00:12:01.053 --> 00:12:04.223
<i>How was I never told</i>
<i>about this secret base?!</i>

192
00:12:04.306 --> 00:12:05.850
Mr. Tokugawa!

193
00:12:06.851 --> 00:12:08.561
Mr. Tokugawa!

194
00:12:10.104 --> 00:12:12.273
I deserve an explanation!

195
00:12:12.857 --> 00:12:15.025
Why. certainly. It's for my creation.

196
00:12:16.026 --> 00:12:18.028
Your… "creation"?

197
00:12:18.112 --> 00:12:19.530
What it is you're making?

198
00:12:19.613 --> 00:12:23.075
{\an8}Exactly 1.000 meters
below the top of the Tree.

199
00:12:23.159 --> 00:12:26.036
{\an8}we are working on building a human being.

200
00:12:26.120 --> 00:12:27.496
Don't tell me…

201
00:12:27.997 --> 00:12:29.540
You wouldn't!

202
00:12:29.623 --> 00:12:31.834
You're not making a clone?

203
00:12:32.334 --> 00:12:35.546
Prime Minister. follow me if you will.

204
00:12:39.216 --> 00:12:41.302
What is this? A mummy?

205
00:12:41.886 --> 00:12:44.388
My goodness. it's huge!

206
00:12:45.890 --> 00:12:47.850
Uh. who am I looking at?

207
00:12:48.350 --> 00:12:50.811
I believe it's someone
that you might know.

208
00:12:50.895 --> 00:12:53.314
<i>He needs no introduction.</i>

209
00:12:53.397 --> 00:12:57.568
He comes from far. far away.
from Kumamoto. in fact.

210
00:12:57.651 --> 00:13:01.071
and his name is Musashi Miyamoto.

211
00:13:02.907 --> 00:13:06.327
Keep your voice down!
Are you trying to wake him?

212
00:13:06.410 --> 00:13:07.745
But I jest.

213
00:13:07.828 --> 00:13:11.165
the whole purpose of this project is
to wake him from this slumber.

214
00:13:11.248 --> 00:13:13.459
Musashi Miyamoto?

215
00:13:13.542 --> 00:13:18.380
Our team of experts. led by
the incomparable Dr. John here…

216
00:13:18.464 --> 00:13:19.340
Howdy.

217
00:13:19.423 --> 00:13:22.718
<i>…successfully removed</i>
<i>the fossilized spinal cord</i>

218
00:13:22.802 --> 00:13:25.346
<i>and were able to extract</i>
<i>intact blood vessels.</i>

219
00:13:25.429 --> 00:13:29.266
<i>But even more exciting were</i>
<i>the viable red blood cells that remained.</i>

220
00:13:29.350 --> 00:13:33.854
<i>Essentially. we were able to harvest</i>
<i>soft tissue and proteins from the remains.</i>

221
00:13:33.938 --> 00:13:36.774
It's insane! Stop your research!

222
00:13:36.857 --> 00:13:39.276
The international scientific community
has agreed

223
00:13:39.360 --> 00:13:42.071
human matter should never
be used for clones!

224
00:13:42.154 --> 00:13:44.865
Mr. Prime Minister.

225
00:13:44.949 --> 00:13:46.867
I wonder if you'd have the courage

226
00:13:46.951 --> 00:13:50.412
to say the same thing
in front of Musashi himself.

227
00:13:51.872 --> 00:13:55.167
<i>This grave can be found</i>
<i>in the Kumamoto Prefecture.</i>

228
00:13:55.251 --> 00:13:57.586
<i>a precious cultural heritage site.</i>

229
00:13:58.128 --> 00:14:01.507
<i>However. the remains</i>
<i>once interred here have disappeared.</i>

230
00:14:02.091 --> 00:14:05.177
<i>It was the body of Musashi Miyamoto.</i>

231
00:14:05.761 --> 00:14:09.014
<i>buried here in the second year</i>
<i>of the Shoho Era.</i>

232
00:14:11.517 --> 00:14:14.979
<i>I will never be able to forget</i>
<i>the excitement I felt that day.</i>

233
00:14:16.188 --> 00:14:19.400
<i>The day I got my hands on the spine</i>
<i>of a Tyrannosaurus Rex.</i>

234
00:14:19.483 --> 00:14:21.151
<i>a dream I'd had for years.</i>

235
00:14:21.235 --> 00:14:23.779
<i>At long last. I could finally do it.</i>

236
00:14:23.863 --> 00:14:29.535
<i>Every laboratory or museum that I visited</i>
<i>flatly rejected my proposal</i>

237
00:14:29.618 --> 00:14:31.871
<i>to split the spine.</i>

238
00:14:32.621 --> 00:14:36.041
<i>Their reluctance was something</i>
<i>I simply couldn't understand.</i>

239
00:14:36.125 --> 00:14:40.546
<i>Why are so many paleontologists content</i>
<i>with just displaying their specimens?</i>

240
00:14:40.629 --> 00:14:43.757
<i>Why conduct your examinations</i>
<i>from the outside?</i>

241
00:14:43.841 --> 00:14:46.218
<i>The interior has so much to tell us.</i>

242
00:14:46.302 --> 00:14:48.554
<i>The spinal cord. The skull.</i>

243
00:14:48.637 --> 00:14:50.055
<i>The eggs.</i>

244
00:14:50.139 --> 00:14:52.433
Why not split the specimens open?

245
00:14:52.516 --> 00:14:54.643
What's the most important part of the egg?

246
00:14:54.727 --> 00:14:57.313
It's not what you can see.
but what's inside.

247
00:14:57.396 --> 00:14:58.814
The shell is just a capsule!

248
00:14:59.982 --> 00:15:02.359
<i>And my reasoning was sound.</i>

249
00:15:02.902 --> 00:15:08.324
Indeed. the experiments I administered
went beyond my expectations.

250
00:15:08.991 --> 00:15:10.993
<i>At the time. it was common knowledge</i>

251
00:15:11.076 --> 00:15:14.204
<i>that only the hard elements</i>
<i>of a body could fossilize.</i>

252
00:15:14.288 --> 00:15:16.332
<i>such as bones. teeth. and eggs.</i>

253
00:15:16.999 --> 00:15:19.585
There came a day
that knowledge was overturned.

254
00:15:19.668 --> 00:15:21.337
<i>When I found soft tissue.</i>

255
00:15:21.420 --> 00:15:25.090
<i>I discovered blood vessels</i>
<i>inside the spilt fossil of a spine.</i>

256
00:15:25.174 --> 00:15:29.094
and that spinal tissue was
more than 70 million years old.

257
00:15:29.720 --> 00:15:33.349
The vessels were still flexible.
They could even be stretched.

258
00:15:33.432 --> 00:15:37.853
Furthermore. when I analyzed the proteins
from the fibers attached to the bones.

259
00:15:37.937 --> 00:15:41.857
<i>I found the amino acids</i>
<i>and their chain sequence.</i>

260
00:15:41.941 --> 00:15:44.026
In fact. I was the one who discovered

261
00:15:44.109 --> 00:15:47.363
that dinosaurs share
a distinct genetic relationship to birds.

262
00:15:47.446 --> 00:15:49.365
<i>It was only a matter of time</i>

263
00:15:49.448 --> 00:15:52.618
<i>before I'd be able to extract</i>
<i>genes and DNA.</i>

264
00:15:52.701 --> 00:15:58.123
<i>Yes. creating living clones of dinosaurs</i>
<i>was no longer a pipe dream.</i>

265
00:15:58.207 --> 00:16:00.626
<i>And so I publicly presented my thesis.</i>

266
00:16:00.709 --> 00:16:02.878
<i>and the response was tremendous.</i>

267
00:16:03.837 --> 00:16:06.131
<i>Just four days after my presentation.</i>

268
00:16:06.215 --> 00:16:09.134
<i>I was paid a visit</i>
<i>by a gentleman from Tokyo.</i>

269
00:16:09.718 --> 00:16:14.139
<i>He arrived with a trunk full of cash.</i>
<i>He explained that it was a deposit.</i>

270
00:16:14.223 --> 00:16:16.934
You really think that money will buy me?

271
00:16:17.017 --> 00:16:18.143
I'm insulted!

272
00:16:19.061 --> 00:16:22.147
<i>But that amount of money</i>
<i>was nothing to be insulted by.</i>

273
00:16:24.525 --> 00:16:26.902
<i>What I found waiting for me in Tokyo</i>

274
00:16:26.986 --> 00:16:28.862
<i>was a small. sharp-eyed man</i>

275
00:16:28.946 --> 00:16:31.824
<i>who looked like he had stepped</i>
<i>out of a samurai movie.</i>

276
00:16:32.324 --> 00:16:34.702
<i>His code name was "Noble Elder."</i>

277
00:16:35.244 --> 00:16:36.662
I would like you to help me.

278
00:16:36.745 --> 00:16:39.206
<i>At first. I didn't understand</i>
<i>what he was asking.</i>

279
00:16:39.289 --> 00:16:41.917
<i>But then. he cut to the chase</i>
<i>and asked me directly.</i>

280
00:16:42.001 --> 00:16:43.419
<i>And this is what he said</i>…

281
00:16:43.502 --> 00:16:45.421
I want to make a human.

282
00:16:46.005 --> 00:16:49.008
<i>Since he was making this request</i>
<i>of a paleontologist.</i>

283
00:16:49.091 --> 00:16:52.177
<i>he wasn't talking about practices</i>
<i>or personalities.</i>

284
00:16:52.261 --> 00:16:55.222
<i>No. he was proposing human cloning.</i>

285
00:16:55.723 --> 00:16:59.059
<i>The international consensus</i>
<i>on cloning of human genetic materials</i>

286
00:16:59.143 --> 00:17:00.936
<i>was that it was clearly taboo.</i>

287
00:17:01.020 --> 00:17:03.480
<i>I was defending this logic as common sense</i>

288
00:17:03.564 --> 00:17:06.442
<i>when I heard something</i>
<i>that made me doubt my own ears.</i>

289
00:17:06.525 --> 00:17:09.945
{\an8}I will provide the remains
of Musashi Miyamoto.

290
00:17:12.906 --> 00:17:16.952
<i>I was visibly stunned</i>
<i>by this out-of-nowhere name drop.</i>

291
00:17:17.036 --> 00:17:19.580
<i>Naturally I knew who Musashi Miyamoto was.</i>

292
00:17:20.205 --> 00:17:22.541
<i>The most famous swordsman in history.</i>

293
00:17:22.624 --> 00:17:24.418
<i>The legendary samurai.</i>

294
00:17:24.501 --> 00:17:27.087
<i>A symbol of historical significance.</i>

295
00:17:27.171 --> 00:17:30.090
- Will you have a look?
- Yes. I want to see it!

296
00:17:30.174 --> 00:17:32.051
Considering the fossils
you've been working on.

297
00:17:32.134 --> 00:17:33.844
he may as well be flesh and blood.

298
00:17:34.803 --> 00:17:38.348
<i>That shock was just a prelude</i>
<i>of things to come.</i>

299
00:17:39.141 --> 00:17:44.104
<i>A huge facility had been prepared for me</i>
<i>366 meters underground.</i>

300
00:17:44.188 --> 00:17:45.481
<i>It was spectacular.</i>

301
00:17:45.564 --> 00:17:49.234
<i>By far the most advanced</i>
<i>experimental facility that I'd ever seen.</i>

302
00:17:49.777 --> 00:17:52.112
<i>The scale. the equipment.</i>

303
00:17:52.196 --> 00:17:55.199
<i>all of it was so incredible.</i>
<i>it was unbelievable.</i>

304
00:17:57.034 --> 00:18:00.329
<i>Behind a series</i>
<i>of highly reinforced doors.</i>

305
00:18:00.412 --> 00:18:03.123
<i>there Musashi lie as if in a deep sleep.</i>

306
00:18:07.711 --> 00:18:09.129
Allow me to explain.

307
00:18:09.213 --> 00:18:11.006
<i>The awe was so profound</i>

308
00:18:11.090 --> 00:18:13.884
<i>that the old man's words</i>
<i>no longer reached my ears.</i>

309
00:18:13.967 --> 00:18:17.888
<i>The tower aboveground</i>
<i>was nothing more than camouflage.</i>

310
00:18:18.472 --> 00:18:20.891
<i>634 meters tall.</i>

311
00:18:20.974 --> 00:18:23.894
<i>Six-three-four in Japanese</i>
<i>can be read as Musashi.</i>

312
00:18:23.977 --> 00:18:25.270
<i>naming it after him.</i>

313
00:18:25.354 --> 00:18:29.399
<i>The structure features a spiral</i>
<i>that can be seen when peering up at it.</i>

314
00:18:29.483 --> 00:18:32.903
<i>representative of</i>
<i>the twisting double-helix of DNA.</i>

315
00:18:33.487 --> 00:18:37.199
<i>But all those cleverly hidden secrets</i>
<i>didn't matter at all to me.</i>

316
00:18:37.908 --> 00:18:38.909
Noble Elder.

317
00:18:40.536 --> 00:18:42.412
- Huh?
- I don't need the money.

318
00:18:42.496 --> 00:18:44.164
Just let me do it.

319
00:18:44.248 --> 00:18:46.667
I know I can.
I will bring him back to life.

320
00:18:47.835 --> 00:18:49.670
{\an8}Even if it goes against God's will?

321
00:18:49.753 --> 00:18:52.172
<i>At the prospect of dazzling immortality.</i>

322
00:18:52.923 --> 00:18:56.677
<i>I turned my back on God</i>
<i>without a moment's hesitation.</i>

323
00:18:56.760 --> 00:18:59.346
Oh. thank you. Thank you. Noble Elder!

324
00:19:02.891 --> 00:19:04.810
DIE. BAKI

325
00:19:06.895 --> 00:19:10.649
<i>Baki had completed</i>
<i>his regular training for the day.</i>

326
00:19:10.732 --> 00:19:13.318
<i>He was so exhausted.</i>
<i>he could scarcely move.</i>

327
00:19:13.986 --> 00:19:17.823
<i>He was enjoying the sound</i>
<i>of his own heartbeat in his chest.</i>

328
00:19:20.409 --> 00:19:22.828
<i>Then something echoed in the boy's ears.</i>

329
00:19:22.911 --> 00:19:25.664
<i>a reverberation</i>
<i>different from his own heartbeat.</i>

330
00:19:25.747 --> 00:19:28.083
<i>An unrelenting rhythm.</i>

331
00:19:31.670 --> 00:19:32.880
<i>That's not</i>

332
00:19:33.672 --> 00:19:35.090
<i>my heartbeat.</i>

333
00:19:36.216 --> 00:19:37.593
<i>Who the hell's is it?</i>

334
00:19:39.678 --> 00:19:41.847
<i>Huh? Who could it belong to?</i>

335
00:19:45.767 --> 00:19:48.353
<i>What am I hearing?</i>
<i>Whose heartbeat is this?</i>

336
00:19:49.938 --> 00:19:51.607
<i>It's not any beat I know.</i>

337
00:19:51.690 --> 00:19:53.400
<i>It's… it's different.</i>

338
00:19:53.483 --> 00:19:54.610
<i>It's none of them.</i>

339
00:19:54.693 --> 00:19:57.112
<i>With painstaking care.</i>

340
00:19:57.196 --> 00:20:01.617
<i>the spinal cord of master swordsman</i>
<i>Musashi Miyamoto was removed.</i>

341
00:20:01.700 --> 00:20:05.204
<i>It appeared almost more feline in shape</i>
<i>than human.</i>

342
00:20:05.704 --> 00:20:11.210
<i>In fact. its shape was reminiscent of that</i>
<i>of large cats like lions or tigers.</i>

343
00:20:11.293 --> 00:20:12.794
My God. look at it!

344
00:20:12.878 --> 00:20:15.297
It's in even better condition
then I could've imagined!

345
00:20:15.380 --> 00:20:18.634
I agree. Professor. But all the same.
isn't it too thick for a human?

346
00:20:19.259 --> 00:20:22.638
And the shape… It doesn't even look like
it came from a hominid.

347
00:20:22.721 --> 00:20:25.098
Skeletons can be quite eloquent.

348
00:20:25.182 --> 00:20:28.143
The shape and size of the bones
can be seen as testaments.

349
00:20:28.810 --> 00:20:31.647
<i>They show the owner's</i>
<i>life practices and activities.</i>

350
00:20:31.730 --> 00:20:34.149
If that hypothesis proves to be true.

351
00:20:34.233 --> 00:20:36.485
this must be the spine of a samurai.

352
00:20:36.568 --> 00:20:39.154
We don't see the skin
or the muscle beneath it.

353
00:20:39.238 --> 00:20:41.907
<i>His training was so rigorous.</i>
<i>he changed his skeleton.</i>

354
00:20:41.990 --> 00:20:44.785
<i>That was the daily life</i>
<i>of this legendary swordsman.</i>

355
00:20:44.868 --> 00:20:47.496
<i>I wonder what his face</i>
<i>looked like as a result.</i>

356
00:20:47.579 --> 00:20:50.415
<i>The self-portrait left behind</i>
<i>is too stylized.</i>

357
00:20:50.499 --> 00:20:53.252
<i>I wish that da Vinci</i>
<i>or Vermeer had painted him.</i>

358
00:20:53.752 --> 00:20:56.588
Have you forgotten. Mr. Nonomura?

359
00:20:56.672 --> 00:20:59.424
We don't need a portrait
to know what the man looked like.

360
00:21:00.050 --> 00:21:01.677
<i>Because. with his DNA.</i>

361
00:21:01.760 --> 00:21:04.930
<i>we will create a living.</i>
<i>breathing. Mr. Musashi!</i>

362
00:21:10.727 --> 00:21:12.020
Pr… Professor!

363
00:21:12.104 --> 00:21:14.189
Please come take a look. Mr. Nonomura.

364
00:21:14.856 --> 00:21:16.608
You don't even need a microscope.

365
00:21:16.692 --> 00:21:19.319
You can see the arteries
with the naked eye.

366
00:21:19.403 --> 00:21:21.530
You're right. I can see it.

367
00:21:21.613 --> 00:21:23.949
I can even see
the elasticity you talked about.

368
00:21:24.032 --> 00:21:26.994
Mr. Tokugawa was
absolutely right about this.

369
00:21:27.077 --> 00:21:28.745
These remains aren't mummified.

370
00:21:28.829 --> 00:21:29.955
It's almost flesh!

371
00:21:30.539 --> 00:21:34.459
Just look at how abnormally thick
his vessels and arteries were!

372
00:21:35.544 --> 00:21:38.630
We will become the parents
of a brand-new Mr. Musashi!

373
00:21:38.714 --> 00:21:39.965
Be careful.

374
00:21:42.843 --> 00:21:45.429
<i>All right. how long</i>
<i>has this been going on?</i>

375
00:21:45.512 --> 00:21:48.473
<i>As usual. I've already run</i>
<i>more than 25 miles.</i>

376
00:21:49.349 --> 00:21:51.268
<i>I can't blame it on overtraining.</i>

377
00:21:51.768 --> 00:21:53.061
<i>Moving my body.</i>

378
00:21:53.145 --> 00:21:55.480
<i>that's the only way</i>
<i>that I can heal myself.</i>

379
00:21:55.564 --> 00:21:57.774
<i>Oh! Oh. here it comes again?</i>

380
00:21:58.275 --> 00:22:00.736
<i>And at the tail end of a full marathon.</i>

381
00:22:07.909 --> 00:22:08.744
Hmm.

382
00:22:10.329 --> 00:22:12.581
<i>That mysterious heartbeat.</i>

383
00:22:12.664 --> 00:22:14.708
<i>the yawning that won't quit</i>…

384
00:22:14.791 --> 00:22:16.460
<i>Just what is this?</i>

385
00:22:16.960 --> 00:22:18.837
<i>I feel like something's coming.</i>

386
00:23:34.246 --> 00:23:35.247
{\an8}<i>Yeah</i>

387
00:23:35.330 --> 00:23:38.125
{\an8}<i>Yeah. yeah </i>

388
00:23:38.625 --> 00:23:41.461
{\an8}<i>I'm on the mountaintop. yeah </i>

389
00:23:41.545 --> 00:23:44.548
{\an8}<i>Yeah. yeah</i>

390
00:23:44.631 --> 00:23:47.467
{\an8}<i>I'm on the mountaintop. yeah</i>

